  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Chase (GUO et al., 2021) is a dataset for the cross-database contextdependent Text-to-SQL problem in Chinese.",
    "It consists of 5,459 question sequences (17,940 questions) over 280 databases, in which only 35% of questions are context-independent, and 28% of SQL queries are easy.",
    "Each question in Chase has rich semantic annotations, including its SQL query, contextual dependency, and schema linking.",
    "Finally, the sql-create-context dataset also addresses the Text-to-SQL task, and was built from WikiSQL and Spider.",
    "foot_3 It contains 78,577 examples of NL queries, SQL CREATE TABLE statements, and SQL Queries answering the questions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Chase (GUO et al., 2021) is a dataset for the cross-database contextdependent Text-to-SQL problem in Chinese."
  ]
}